<item>
            <title>[JDK-8303422] Use common functions to exit the VM for -Xshare:dump and CDS errors</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8303422</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>When running in -Xshare:dump mode, we need to exit the VM process in a special way&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
One example is here:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/openjdk/jdk/blob/1fdaf252b6375773072e665fd5d4cfb509e98f4c/src/hotspot/share/cds/metaspaceShared.cpp#L567-L571&quot;&gt;https://github.com/openjdk/jdk/blob/1fdaf252b6375773072e665fd5d4cfb509e98f4c/src/hotspot/share/cds/metaspaceShared.cpp#L567-L571&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;// There may be pending VM operations. We have changed some global states&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;// (such as vmClasses::_klasses) that may cause these VM operations&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;// to fail. For safety, forget these operations and exit the VM directly.&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;os::_exit(0);&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
But there are also other calls to exit the VM when an unrecoverable error happens during CDS archive dumping and loading. Currently, we have ad-hoc calls to os::_exit(0), vm_exit_during_initialization() and  vm_direct_exit().&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
We should change all such calls to a few utility functions (used under different situations) with proper documentation.</description>
